How it works:

  1. Upload a .db database file
  2. Set threshold and optional job filter
  3. Click "Analyze Fail Rates"
  4. Explore tabs: Overview, Heatmap, Trends, Detail
  5. Export results as CSV or PDF

Fail criteria: FL + FH are hard failures. OT-, TT, OT+ count as passing.

📊 Summary

Test Criteria & Status Codes

FL Failed Low (120s < min voltage) FAIL
FH Failed High (120s > max voltage) FAIL
OT- Out of Tolerance Negative (< min % change) PASS*
TT Test-to-Test Variability (> max pairwise dev) PASS*
OT+ Out of Tolerance Positive (> max % change) PASS*

* These codes flag anomalies but are not counted as hard failures in the fail rate calculations.
